wfSysDescr.name: wfSysDescr
wfSysDescr.description: A textual description of the entity including full name and version of the system's hardware type, OS, and networking SW

wfSysObjectID.name: wfSysObjectID
wfSysObjectID.description: Provides an unambiguous means for determining the MIB type (old product vs. harpoon MIB).

wfSysUpTime.name: wfSysUpTime
wfSysUpTime.description: Time in seconds/100 since the last cold start

wfSysContact.name: wfSysContact
wfSysContact.description: Contact person for this node and where/how to contact them

wfSysName.name: wfSysName
wfSysName.description: Node's fully qualified domain name or administratively assigned name

wfSysServices.name: wfSysServices
wfSysServices.description: A sum of numbers indicating the set of services the entity offers. For each layer L, add 2**(L - 1). Example: 78 = Layers 2,3,4, and 7.

wfSysGmtOffset.name: wfSysGmtOffset
wfSysGmtOffset.description: The positive or negative offset from Greenwich Mean Time (GMT). This effectively describes the time zone.

wfSysMibVersion.name: wfSysMibVersion
wfSysMibVersion.description: The version of the private management information base currently being used by the system software. Format is: xV.RR

wfSysMibRevision.name: wfSysMibRevision
wfSysMibRevision.description: The revision level of the private management information base currently being used by the system software.

wfSysAgentType.name: wfSysAgentType
wfSysAgentType.description: The network management agent's module type

wfSysMaxUpTime.name: wfSysMaxUpTime
wfSysMaxUpTime.description: Time in seconds/100 since the last cold start. Max across slots

wfSysBccHelpFileName.name: wfSysBccHelpFileName
wfSysBccHelpFileName.description: Location of the BCC help file.

wfSysConsoleSlotMask.name: wfSysConsoleSlotMask
wfSysConsoleSlotMask.description: Slot mask defining which slots Console Interface is eligible to run on. The MSBit represents slot 1, the next most significant bit represents slot 2, and so on... Slots can be 1-14. If set to 0, then the Console Interface remains on the first booted slot. Default is all slots on a BCN. Affects only multislot routers with single physical console port.
